<font color="#FF0000">RESPECT</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 28  1:00:11 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
<br>
It sure was a long time ago, back in 68-69.  I came back to a teaching job that i had left behind.  my duty there was on a very secure airbase, thanks to a division of ROK Tigers.  I have always had the greatest respect for the grunts who humped the boonies.  The difficult time for me has been in living with the fact that so many didn't come back, and I did, safe and sound, and took up life pretty normally.  It hurts so bad to see those who have not been able to rid themselves of the demons from long ago.  hardly a day goes by that my mind doesn't return there.
<p><code>-- brbsader@pionet.net  (Brendan R. Burchard) </code><p>


